Tell HN: Twitter Is NSFW by Default?
text:
I signed up for Twitter after the Musk takeover. I use it in a separate, new Firefox container, and I'm only following a few tech influencers on a tech topic I care about.

About 50% of my Twitter feed is:

  - soccer fights

  - videos of people beating the crap out of each other in the street

  - straight-up pornography
Is this expected? How do I turn it off so I can see more of the content I signed up for and less street fighting and porn?

Looking for an Explanation on US Trends
text: As somebody not personally involved in American politics and culture can anybody explain to me why Kanye West is dropped by Adidas for making offensive, antisemitic comments but Balenciaga is defended by NY Times Fashion writers after their ad campaign based on child abuse innuendo? Why is speech involving antisemitism a cancel worthy offense while at the same time advertising based on the provocation of horrific child abuse is excused and explained as artistic expression. What is in the water these days?
